.TH "TINYRAD" "3" "@RELEASE_MONTH@" "@PACKAGE_NAME@" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
tinyrad - Tiny RADIUS Client Library

.SH LIBRARY
TinyRad (libtinyrad, -ltinyrad)

.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB#include\fR \fB<tinyrad.h>\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
Remote Authentication Dial-In User Service (RADIUS) (RFC 2865 and RFC 2866)
is a networking protocol that provides authentication, authorization, and
accounting (AAA) for users connected to network devices.  The Tiny RDAIUS
Client Library (tinyrad) is a small, RFC compliant implementation of the RADIUS
protocol.

.SH INDEX

.TP 25
.BR tinyrad_get_option (3)
retrieves global and instance parameters used by the TinyRad library.

.TP
.BR tinyrad_memfree (3)
releases memory allocated by TinyRad routines.

.TP
.BR tinyrad_set_option (3)
sets global and instance parameters used by the TinyRad library.

.TP
.BR tinyrad_strerror (3)
returns an error message corresponding to an error code

.TP
.BR tinyrad_strerror_r (3)
copies into a buffer an error message corresponding to an error code

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR tinyrad (1),
.BR tinyrad_error (3),
.BR tinyrad_options (3)

